# Rutter

Git-backed Skill Registry and Query CLI for meta-agent.

Rutter manages atomic skills for meta-agent's selective injection system. It provides registry indexing, validation, search, and the foundation for an MCP-friendly query layer.

Current package version: `0.2.0`

## Design Assets

| Asset | Location | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Active Plans | `.design/plans/` | Current execution plans (PRDs) |
| Wiki | `.design/wiki/` | Detailed design knowledge |
| History | `.design/history/` | Completed / archived plans |
| Changelog | `CHANGELOG.md` | Latest changes and active plans |

## Skills

| Skill | Version | Description |
|---|---|---|
| [Game Migration](skills/game-migration/README.md) | v0.1 | Migrate existing games onto Rust headless framework + engine architecture |

## Registry CLI

```bash
# Validate the registry
python -m rutter validate --path .

# Rebuild registry/index.yaml
python -m rutter build-index --path .

# Search skills and metadata
python -m rutter search parity --path .

# List indexed skill families
python -m rutter list-families --path .

# Fetch one family or one skill payload
python -m rutter get-family game-migration --path .
python -m rutter get-skill game_migration_verify --path .

# Inspect direct dependencies for one skill
python -m rutter get-dependencies game_migration_verify --path .

# Start the MCP server over stdio
uv run --extra mcp python -m rutter serve --path .
```

Registry assets live under `registry/<family>/<version>/`.

The query functions under `src/rutter/query.py` are the stable read-only surface intended to be wrapped by a future MCP server.
The MCP server implementation now lives in `src/rutter/mcp_server.py` and is exposed through `python -m rutter serve`.

## Release Status

- `0.2.0`: registry foundation, read-only query layer, and MCP server are implemented
- bundled skill family: `game-migration@v0.1`

## Usage

Skills in this repo are living documents. Update them as migration practices evolve.

### meta-agent Workflow

```bash
# Check current state
meta-agent status

# Run pending tasks
meta-agent run --working-dir .

# Query available skills from rutter before selecting runtime skills
python -m rutter search migration --path .
```
